        "detail": "Three structural findings addressed:\n\n(1) No automated enforcement of cross-zone layering → FIXED: Created scripts/check-zone-layering.sh. Enforces that the three GoToBedKit application zones are mutually isolated: Scheduler zone (Sources/GoToBed/Scheduler/) may not reference Overlay or Settings-UI types; Overlay zone (Sources/GoToBed/Overlay/) may not reference Settings-UI types or SchedulerEngine; Settings-UI zone (Sources/GoToBed/UI/) may not reference Overlay types or SchedulerEngine. AppEnvironment remains the sole composition root that wires all zones together — any cross-zone coupling that bypasses it will be caught before merge.\n\n(2) Full inter-service event chain untested → ALREADY ADDRESSED by previous task (InterServiceWiringTests.swift, added to GoToBedTests). Tests cover the Store→SchedulerEngine→onFire closure→OverlayController path and the shutdown contract.\n\n(3) GoToBedCore UI-framework constraint not machine-enforced → ALREADY ADDRESSED by existing scripts/check-core-purity.sh (enforces no AppKit/SwiftUI/Cocoa/UIKit in Sources/GoToBedCore/).\n\nNew script wired into Makefile validate target: ./scripts/verify-no-network.sh → ./scripts/check-core-purity.sh → bash ./scripts/check-zone-layering.sh → sh ./scripts/check-site-docs.sh. All 59 tests pass, all validation scripts pass."
