        "content": "feat(arch): add automated cross-zone layering enforcement for GoToBedKit\n\nAdd scripts/check-zone-layering.sh, a CI guard that enforces the three\nintra-module zone boundaries within GoToBedKit. Within a single Swift\nmodule there are no import statements between files, so zone isolation\nis expressed as \"zone X must not reference types defined in zone Y.\"\nThe script makes that constraint machine-checkable via word-boundary grep.\n\nEnforced rules:\n- Scheduler zone (Sources/GoToBed/Scheduler/) must not reference\n  Overlay or Settings-UI types — the scheduler is a pure service.\n- Overlay zone (Sources/GoToBed/Overlay/) must not reference\n  Settings-UI types or SchedulerEngine — it is a standalone presentation\n  component wired by the composition root.\n- Settings-UI zone (Sources/GoToBed/UI/) must not reference Overlay\n  types or SchedulerEngine — settings views access those only through\n  the AppEnvironment composition root, never by direct type reference.\n\nAppEnvironment remains the sole file that is intentionally permitted to\nreference all zones together. Any cross-zone coupling that bypasses it\nwill now be caught before a PR merges.\n\nWired into: make validate (after check-core-purity.sh, before check-site-docs.sh).\nAll 59 tests and all validation scripts pass.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>\n"
